Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Cut @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Peel @red onion{1}, then mince until you have 2 TBSP minced onion (use the rest as you like). Finely chop @chives{¼%ounce}.

Toss sweet potatoes with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} on a #baking sheet{}. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Crack @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{}, then add minced onion, @ground pork{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{⅓%cup}, @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tablespoon}, and a big pinch of salt (we sent more panko and egg than needed). Gently mix just until combined. Shape into two 1-inch-tall meatloaves and place on baking sheet with sweet potatoes.

Put @BBQ sauce{1%teaspoon} in another medium bowl and set aside, then use the rest of the @BBQ sauce{¼%cup} to brush meatloaves on baking sheet. Place sheet in oven and bake until sweet potatoes are tender and meatloaves are cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}, tossing sweet potatoes halfway through.

Add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce} to bowl with barbecue sauce, followed by @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @white wine vinegar{1%teaspoon} (we sent more), @sugar{½%teaspoon}, and salt and pepper to taste. Toss to combine. Set aside until rest of meal is ready.

> While you're waiting, brainstorm ways to use the extra egg: scrambled, poached, green with a side of ham—the possibilities are endless!

Divide meatloaves, sweet potatoes, and slaw between plates. Sprinkle chives over everything and serve.